## Phase 6: Smart PDF Processing Pipeline
**Effort: Very Large | Risk: High**

> [!WARNING]
> This phase involves R2 integration, embedding generation, and background job scheduling. It should be implemented last and can be deferred if needed.

### Architecture

```
User uploads PDF
       ↓
[Layer 1: Cheap indexing — one-time]
  lopdf/pdfium → extract text blocks + image refs
  Store chunks in Postgres with has_image flag
  Store images in R2
  Generate embeddings (small model)
       ↓
[Layer 2: On-demand AI — per query]
  User query → embedding search → top chunks
  If chunk.has_image → selective vision call
  Generate answer with relevant context only
       ↓
[Cleanup: 10-minute TTL]
  Background job flushes R2 objects + Postgres chunks
```

### New Backend Components

#### [NEW] `crates/pdf_indexer/src/lib.rs`
- Parse PDF into `PdfChunk` structs with `has_image` flag
- Extract and store images separately in R2
- Generate embeddings via small embedding model API

#### [MODIFY] Storage crate
- `insert_pdf_chunks(chunks: Vec<PdfChunk>)` → Postgres
- `search_chunks_by_embedding(query_embedding, top_k)` → vector similarity
- `flush_expired_pdf_data(older_than: Duration)` → cleanup job

#### [NEW] Background cleanup job
- Runs every 5 minutes
- Deletes R2 objects and Postgres chunks older than 10 minutes post-lesson-creation

